#+TITLE: Image tests for the Self-Supervised Classification Network

The repository has scripts for running these tests - have a look at the [[README.md]] however these require some distributed network to run.
Therefore the aim is to run these tests locally without the need for the distributed GPU load.

import torch

import torch.backends.cudnn as cudnn
#+end_src

seed = 100
torch.manual_seed(seed)
torch.cuda.manual_seed_all(args.seed)
np.random.seed(args.seed)
random.seed(args.seed)

arch='resnet50'
base_model = torchvision_models.__dict__[arch]()
backbone_dim = base_model.fc.weight.shape[1]
dim=128
gpu=None
eps=1e-12
weight_decay=1e-6

sys.stdout = utils.PrintMultiple(sys.stdout, open(os.path.join(args.save_path, 'log.txt'), 'a+'))

model = Model(base_model=base_model,
              dim=dim,
              hidden_dim=4096,
              cls_size=[1000, 2000, 4000, 8000],
              num_cls=4,
              num_hidden=2,
              use_bn=True,
              backbone_dim=backbone_dim,
              fixed_cls=False,
              no_leaky=False
              )

print(model)

nn_queue = utils.NNQueue(262144, dim, gpu)

model = torch.nn.DataParallel(model).cuda()

criterion = Loss(row_tau=0.1, col_tau=0.05, eps=eps).cuda(gpu)
params_groups = model.parameters()

optimizer = torch.optim.SGD(params_groups, 4.8, momentum=0.9, weight_decay)
optimizer = LARC(optimizer=optimizer, trust_coefficient=0.001, clip=False)

cudnn.benchmark = True # enable finding the optimal algorithm
